  "text": "# TLS Configuration Flow: Prometheus to HTTP Clients\n\nThe TLS configuration for HTTP connections in Prometheus flows from configuration structures through factory functions to Go's standard `crypto/tls.Config`.\n\n## Configuration Definitions\n\n**prometheus/prometheus/config/config.go:**\n- `ScrapeConfig` (line 747) contains an embedded `HTTPClientConfig` field for scrape targets\n- `RemoteWriteConfig` (line 1419) contains an embedded `HTTPClientConfig` field for remote write endpoints\n\nBoth of these import `HTTPClientConfig` and `TLSConfig` from `github.com/prometheus/common/config` (line 33 import)\n\n**prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:**\n- `HTTPClientConfig` struct (lines 75-86) contains a `TLSConfig` field (line 85)\n- `TLSConfig` struct (lines 328-339) defines the configuration with fields:\n  - `CAFile`: Path to CA certificate\n  - `CertFile`: Path to client certificate\n  - `KeyFile`: Path to client key\n  - `ServerName`: Server name for verification\n  - `InsecureSkipVerify`: Skip certificate verification flag\n\n## Scrape Configuration Flow\n\n1. **Configuration Loading** (prometheus/prometheus/config/config.go):\n   - `ScrapeConfig` is defined with embedded `HTTPClientConfig` containing `TLSConfig`\n   - The configuration is loaded from YAML and validated\n\n2. **Scrape Pool Creation** (prometheus/prometheus/scrape/scrape.go):\n   - `newScrapePool()` function (line 138) receives `*config.ScrapeConfig`\n   - At line 155, it calls `newScrapeClient(cfg.HTTPClientConfig, cfg.JobName, options.HTTPClientOptions...)`\n\n3. **HTTP Client Creation** (prometheus/prometheus/scrape/scrape.go):\n   - `newScrapeClient()` function (line 2260) receives `config_util.HTTPClientConfig`\n   - At line 2261, it calls `config_util.NewClientFromConfig(cfg, name, optFuncs...)`\n   - This imports `config_util` as `github.com/prometheus/common/config` (line 27)\n\n4. **RoundTripper and TLS Configuration** (prometheus-common/config/http_config.go):\n   - `NewClientFromConfig()` (line 125) calls `NewRoundTripperFromConfig(cfg, name, disableKeepAlives)`\n   - `NewRoundTripperFromConfig()` (line 135) is the key function:\n     - At line 172, it calls `NewTLSConfig(&cfg.TLSConfig)`\n     - Returns the converted `*tls.Config` at line 179\n     - Uses the result to configure `http.Transport.TLSClientConfig` (line 144)\n     - Creates an `http.Transport` with the TLS configuration\n\n5. **TLS Config Conversion** (prometheus-common/config/http_config.go):\n   - `NewTLSConfig()` (line 293) converts the custom `TLSConfig` to Go's `*tls.Config`:\n     - Sets `InsecureSkipVerify` (line 294)\n     - Reads and parses CA certificate if provided (lines 298-305)\n     - Sets `ServerName` for certificate verification (lines 308-310)\n     - Loads and validates client certificate/key pair (lines 312-322)\n     - Returns the fully configured `*tls.Config`\n\n6. **Dynamic CA Reloading** (prometheus-common/config/http_config.go):\n   - For CA files, a `tlsRoundTripper` wrapper (line 377) is created (line 182)\n   - This monitors the CA file for changes and updates the TLS configuration dynamically (line 424-455)\n\n## Remote Write Configuration Flow\n\n1. **Configuration Loading** (prometheus/prometheus/config/config.go):\n   - `RemoteWriteConfig` (line 1419) contains embedded `HTTPClientConfig` with `TLSConfig`\n\n2. **Remote Write Setup** (prometheus/prometheus/storage/remote/write.go):\n   - `ApplyConfig()` method processes remote write configurations (line 140)\n   - For each `RemoteWriteConfig`, it creates a `ClientConfig` struct (line 169)\n   - At line 173, the `RemoteWriteConfig.HTTPClientConfig` is passed to `ClientConfig.HTTPClientConfig`\n\n3. **Write Client Creation** (prometheus/prometheus/storage/remote/client.go):\n   - `NewWriteClient()` (line 183) receives the `ClientConfig` with `HTTPClientConfig`\n   - At line 188, it calls `config_util.NewClientFromConfig(conf.HTTPClientConfig, \"remote_storage_write_client\", httpOpts...)`\n   - From here, the flow is identical to scraping: `NewRoundTripperFromConfig()` → `NewTLSConfig()`\n\n4. **Read Client Creation** (prometheus/prometheus/storage/remote/client.go):\n   - `NewReadClient()` (line 151) similarly calls `config_util.NewClientFromConfig()` with the same flow\n\n## Key Validation Points\n\n**prometheus/prometheus/cmd/promtool/main.go:**\n- `checkTLSConfig()` function (line 790) validates that:\n  - If a client cert file is provided, a key file must also be provided\n  - If a key file is provided, a cert file must also be provided\n\n**prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:**\n- `HTTPClientConfig.Validate()` (line 90) ensures only one authentication method is configured\n- `NewTLSConfig()` validates certificate files and loads them into memory\n- `TLSConfig.getClientCertificate()` (line 348) loads client certificates from disk\n\n## TLS Features Supported\n\n1. **Certificate Authority**: CA file verification of server certificates\n2. **Client Certificates**: Mutual TLS (mTLS) with client certificate and key\n3. **Server Name Indication (SNI)**: Custom ServerName for hostname verification\n4. **Insecure Mode**: Skip certificate validation when needed\n5. **Dynamic Reloading**: CA certificates are reloaded if the file changes (using MD5 hash comparison)\n6. **RoundTripper Wrapping**: Bearer token, basic auth, and custom headers can be layered on top of TLS\n\n## File Paths Summary\n\n- prometheus-common defines the configuration structures and conversion logic\n- prometheus uses these structures in scrape and remote write configurations\n- The conversion from custom TLSConfig to Go's tls.Config happens in prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:NewTLSConfig()\n- Both scraping and remote write/read use the same HTTPClientConfig and TLSConfig mechanisms"
